  Changes

  chttp.h — HttpRequest.fd

  Added int fd as the first field. Set by connection_thread immediately before dispatch so handlers (including forked ones) can access the raw
  client socket.

  chttp.c — two edits in connection_thread

  1. req.fd = fd; — wires up the new field.
  if (res.status != 0)
      chttp_write_response(fd, &res);
  2. status == 0 is the sentinel meaning "a forked child already wrote the response; don't write again."

  server.c — fork infrastructure

  g_server_fd — stored after chttp_server_init so children can close the listening socket immediately (preventing them from accidentally accepting
  new connections).

  fork_and_run(req, res, handler, username)

